@startuml ProbationClassification_SP_ProbationPreprocess
title CTS_GeneralNormalClassification_Probation_Preprocess - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #FFE0B2
skinparam activityBorderColor #FF6F00

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_GeneralNormalClassification_Probation_Preprocess
  **Database**: bodb_VR2Model.wsv_cts (SQL Server)
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
  **Parameters**: Customer list (comma-separated string)
  **Called From**: ProbationClassifCriteria
  **Purpose**: Re-classify customers in probation period
end note

partition "Input Processing" {
  :Receive Customer List;
  note right
    **Input Format**: Comma-separated CustIDs
    **Example**: "123456,789012,345678,901234"
    
    **Source**: Customers from ProbationScan
  end note

  :Parse CustID String;
  note right
    **SQL Server Parsing**:
    ```sql
    -- Split string into rows
    DECLARE @CustIDs TABLE (CustID BIGINT)
    
    INSERT INTO @CustIDs
    SELECT value
    FROM STRING_SPLIT(@ListCustId, ',')
    ```
    
    **Result**: Table variable with one CustID per row
  end note

  :Create #TempProbationCustomers;
  note right
    **Temp Table**:
    - CustID (bigint)
    - Used for joining with other tables
    - Improves query performance
  end note
}

partition "Get Current Classification" {
  :Retrieve Current Customer Data;
  note right
    **Query**:
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      c.CustID,
      c.CTSCustID,
      c.CategoryID AS CurrentCategoryID,
      c.CategoryName AS CurrentCategoryName,
      c.ProbationStartDate,
      c.ProbationEndDate,
      c.TurnoverRM AS BaselineTurnoverRM,
      c.WinlossRM AS BaselineWinlossRM,
      c.BetCount AS BaselineBetCount,
      c.ActiveDays AS BaselineActiveDays
    FROM CTSCustomerClassification c
    WHERE c.CustID IN (SELECT CustID FROM @CustIDs)
      AND c.ProbationEndDate > GETDATE()
    ```
    
    **Purpose**: Get baseline classification and probation info
  end note

  :Store in #CurrentClassification;
}

partition "Calculate Probation Performance" {
  :Query Customer Transactions;
  note right
    **Get Betting Activity During Probation**:
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      c.CustID,
      SUM(t.TurnoverRM) AS TurnoverDuringProbation,
      SUM(t.WinlossRM) AS WinlossDuringProbation,
      COUNT(t.BetID) AS BetCountDuringProbation,
      COUNT(DISTINCT CAST(t.BetDate AS DATE)) AS ActiveDaysDuringProbation,
      AVG(t.BetAmount) AS AvgBetSizeDuringProbation,
      MIN(t.BetDate) AS FirstBetDateDuringProbation,
      MAX(t.BetDate) AS LastBetDateDuringProbation
    FROM #CurrentClassification c
    JOIN CustomerTransaction t 
      ON c.CustID = t.CustID
    WHERE t.TransactionDate BETWEEN c.ProbationStartDate AND GETDATE()
      AND t.BetStatus = 'Settled'  -- Only completed bets
      AND t.IsVoid = 0             -- Exclude void bets
    GROUP BY c.CustID
    ```
    
    **Metrics Calculated**:
    - TurnoverRM: Total betting volume
    - WinlossRM: Total profit/loss (negative = customer loss)
    - BetCount: Number of bets placed
    - ActiveDays: Days with betting activity
    - AvgBetSize: Average bet amount
    - Date range: First and last bet
  end note

  :Store in #ProbationPerformance;

  :Calculate Performance Changes;
  note right
    **Compare Baseline vs Probation**:
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      c.*,
      p.TurnoverDuringProbation,
      p.WinlossDuringProbation,
      p.BetCountDuringProbation,
      p.ActiveDaysDuringProbation,
      
      -- Calculate changes (%)
      CASE 
        WHEN c.BaselineTurnoverRM > 0 
        THEN (p.TurnoverDuringProbation - c.BaselineTurnoverRM) 
             / c.BaselineTurnoverRM * 100
        ELSE 0 
      END AS TurnoverChangePercent,
      
      CASE 
        WHEN c.BaselineWinlossRM <> 0 
        THEN (p.WinlossDuringProbation - c.BaselineWinlossRM) 
             / ABS(c.BaselineWinlossRM) * 100
        ELSE 0 
      END AS WinlossChangePercent,
      
      -- Determine improvement/deterioration
      CASE
        WHEN p.WinlossDuringProbation > c.BaselineWinlossRM 
        THEN 'Improved'      -- Less loss or more win
        WHEN p.WinlossDuringProbation < c.BaselineWinlossRM 
        THEN 'Deteriorated'  -- More loss or less win
        ELSE 'Maintained'
      END AS PerformanceTrend
    FROM #CurrentClassification c
    JOIN #ProbationPerformance p ON c.CustID = p.CustID
    ```
    
    **Performance Indicators**:
    - Improved: Better performance (less loss)
    - Deteriorated: Worse performance (more loss)
    - Maintained: Similar performance
  end note

  :Store in #PerformanceAnalysis;
}

partition "Determine New Classification" {
  :Apply Re-Classification Rules;
  note right
    **Re-Classification Matrix**:
    
    **PA (Problem Account) Customers**:
    ```sql
    WHEN CurrentCategoryID = PA AND PerformanceTrend = 'Improved' THEN
      CASE 
        WHEN WinlossDuringProbation > -5000  -- Much improved
        THEN NewCategoryID = Normal
        WHEN WinlossDuringProbation > -10000  -- Improved
        THEN NewCategoryID = PotentialPA
        ELSE NewCategoryID = PA  -- Still problematic
      END
    
    WHEN CurrentCategoryID = PA AND PerformanceTrend = 'Maintained' THEN
      NewCategoryID = PA  -- No improvement, extend probation
    
    WHEN CurrentCategoryID = PA AND PerformanceTrend = 'Deteriorated' THEN
      NewCategoryID = PA  -- Worse, maintain PA, extend probation
    ```
    
    **PotentialPA Customers**:
    ```sql
    WHEN CurrentCategoryID = PotentialPA AND PerformanceTrend = 'Improved' THEN
      CASE 
        WHEN WinlossDuringProbation > 0  -- Profitable now
        THEN NewCategoryID = Normal
        WHEN WinlossDuringProbation > -3000  -- Small loss
        THEN NewCategoryID = Normal
        ELSE NewCategoryID = PotentialPA  -- Still some concern
      END
    
    WHEN CurrentCategoryID = PotentialPA AND PerformanceTrend = 'Deteriorated' THEN
      CASE 
        WHEN WinlossDuringProbation < -10000  -- Much worse
        THEN NewCategoryID = PA
        ELSE NewCategoryID = PotentialPA  -- Minor decline
      END
    ```
    
    **Thresholds (Examples)**:
    - PA → Normal: Winloss > -5,000 RM
    - PA → PotentialPA: Winloss > -10,000 RM
    - PotentialPA → Normal: Winloss > -3,000 RM
    - PotentialPA → PA: Winloss < -10,000 RM
  end note

  :Calculate New Category;
  note right
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      pa.*,
      CASE 
        -- PA Re-classification
        WHEN pa.CurrentCategoryID = @PA_CategoryID THEN
          CASE 
            WHEN pa.WinlossDuringProbation > -5000 THEN @Normal_CategoryID
            WHEN pa.WinlossDuringProbation > -10000 THEN @PotentialPA_CategoryID
            ELSE @PA_CategoryID
          END
        
        -- PotentialPA Re-classification
        WHEN pa.CurrentCategoryID = @PotentialPA_CategoryID THEN
          CASE 
            WHEN pa.WinlossDuringProbation > -3000 THEN @Normal_CategoryID
            WHEN pa.WinlossDuringProbation < -10000 THEN @PA_CategoryID
            ELSE @PotentialPA_CategoryID
          END
        
        ELSE pa.CurrentCategoryID  -- No change
      END AS NewCategoryID
    FROM #PerformanceAnalysis pa
    ```
  end note

  :Determine Probation Action;
  note right
    **Probation Actions**:
    
    1. **Complete Probation** (NewCategoryID = Normal):
       - Customer improved to Normal
       - Clear probation dates
       - Remove probation status
    
    2. **Extend Probation** (NewCategoryID = PA/PotentialPA):
       - Customer still problematic
       - Extend ProbationEndDate by 30 days
       - Continue monitoring
    
    3. **Upgrade Severity** (PotentialPA → PA):
       - Customer deteriorated
       - Change category to PA
       - Extend probation
       - Increase monitoring
    
    ```sql
    NewProbationEndDate = CASE 
      WHEN NewCategoryID IN (@PA_CategoryID, @PotentialPA_CategoryID)
      THEN DATEADD(DAY, 30, GETDATE())  -- Extend 30 days
      ELSE NULL  -- Complete probation
    END
    ```
  end note
}

partition "Update Classification" {
  :UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification;
  note right
    **Update Query**:
    ```sql
    UPDATE c
    SET 
      c.CategoryID = pa.NewCategoryID,
      c.CategoryName = cat.CategoryName,
      c.TurnoverRM = pa.TurnoverDuringProbation,
      c.WinlossRM = pa.WinlossDuringProbation,
      c.BetCount = pa.BetCountDuringProbation,
      c.ActiveDays = pa.ActiveDaysDuringProbation,
      c.ProbationEndDate = pa.NewProbationEndDate,
      c.LastProbationReviewDate = GETDATE(),
      c.UpdatedDate = GETDATE()
    FROM CTSCustomerClassification c
    JOIN #PerformanceAnalysis pa ON c.CustID = pa.CustID
    JOIN CategoryMaster cat ON cat.CategoryID = pa.NewCategoryID
    WHERE c.CustID IN (SELECT CustID FROM @CustIDs)
    ```
    
    **Fields Updated**:
    - CategoryID: New classification
    - CategoryName: New category name
    - Turnover/Winloss/BetCount/ActiveDays: Updated metrics
    - ProbationEndDate: Extended or cleared
    - LastProbationReviewDate: Current timestamp
    - UpdatedDate: Current timestamp
  end note

  :Log Classification Changes;
  note right
    **Insert into ClassificationChangeLog**:
    ```sql
    INSERT INTO CTSClassificationChangeLog
    (CustID, OldCategoryID, NewCategoryID, 
     ChangeReason, ChangeDate, ChangedBy)
    SELECT 
      pa.CustID,
      pa.CurrentCategoryID,
      pa.NewCategoryID,
      'Probation Review: ' + pa.PerformanceTrend,
      GETDATE(),
      'ProbationClassificationJob'
    FROM #PerformanceAnalysis pa
    WHERE pa.CurrentCategoryID <> pa.NewCategoryID
    ```
    
    **Purpose**:
    - Audit trail of category changes
    - Performance tracking
    - Compliance reporting
  end note
}

:Return Success;
note right
  **Completion**:
  - All probation customers re-classified
  - Classification updated in database
  - Changes logged for audit
  - Ready for next batch
end note

note right
  **Re-Classification Summary**:
  
  **Improvement Path** (Downgrade):
  PA → PotentialPA → Normal
  - Based on reduced losses
  - Better betting behavior
  - Complete probation at Normal
  
  **Deterioration Path** (Upgrade):
  Normal → PotentialPA → PA
  - Based on increased losses
  - Worse betting behavior
  - Extended probation
  
  **Key Metrics**:
  - Turnover: Betting volume
  - Winloss: Profit/loss (negative = customer loss)
  - BetCount: Betting frequency
  - ActiveDays: Betting consistency
  
  **Probation Actions**:
  1. **Complete**: Clear probation (Normal)
  2. **Extend**: Add 30 days (PA/PotentialPA)
  3. **Upgrade**: Increase severity (PotentialPA → PA)
  
  **Business Logic**:
  - Focus on customer behavior during probation
  - Compare baseline vs probation performance
  - Determine improvement/deterioration
  - Apply thresholds for category change
  - Extend or complete probation accordingly
  
  **Performance Considerations**:
  - Complex joins and calculations
  - 300-second timeout
  - Batch processing (5000-10000 customers)
  - Indexed tables for efficiency
  
  **Typical Re-Classification Rates**:
  - 30% Improved (downgrade category)
  - 50% Maintained (keep category, extend)
  - 20% Deteriorated (upgrade category)
end note

stop

@enduml

